    Hi all,

I have found that linking with '-lcurses' is preferable to '-ltermcap', which
is what 'configure' comes up with. With the default library, zle behaves badly
on for example a vt220 emulator such as the ones included with Novell's LAN
Workplace or the telnet of IBM's TCPIP for OS/2.

Jos
